Please see this for the initial patch: #4359, this patch makes some optimizations.  
When rewriting, `Tasks` do not need to retain successful tasks for example `RewriteFileGroup` to revert. However, the references to these RewriteFileGroups are currently retained, and the memory will not be released after the rewriting finished. When rewriting the v2 table, a `RewriteFileGroup` may contain a large number of data files and delete files. After the `partial commit` is enabled, the memory overhead of the driver will also increase as the rewrite proceeds. So it makes sense to release memory here.  
